OL,3,CMinister considers law to protect cash
OL,4,Cpayments
OL,6,FDeputy Morel is concerned that Jersey
OL,7,Fgoing cashless would infringe on
OL,8,Fresidents' privacy and particularly
OL,9,Faffect elderly people and those trying
OL,10,Fto budget with cash.
OL,12,FHe explains: "It's my belief that we
OL,13,Fshouldn't lose cash and that's why I'm
OL,14,Fthinking of bringing a proposition to
OL,15,Fensure cash is maintained in Jersey.
OL,17,F"Cash entails privacy and cash gives
OL,18,Fyou a freedom to choose to save in the
OL,19,Fway you want to.
